<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> think better of someone • think better of something</xh5><p> <i>think better of someone</i>—(also: think the better of someone) form a higher opinion of a person: Surely no one could <u>think better of</u> Jason for the quoted remarks?</p><p> <i>think better of something—</i>change one’s mind with regard to smth.: Two years into his residency, Jadali <u>thought better of</u> his decision to become an internist.</p> </entry>
